Meet the Klaus family! If you know our CHRISTkindlmarkt CHS origin…..this is it. Conny, the mom in the photo was 19 years old from Dresden, Germany and landed in our home for a year in 1994. She gifted us for many years an original Erzgebirge Räucherman (handcrafted incense smoker man) from this Christmas Markt pictured here in Dresden. Our young children had favorites in our growing collection. They thought everyone had these in their homes at Christmas. Fast forward 26 years later CHRISTkindlmarkt CHS is founded and offering Räuchermen and more traditions to you! 
They have been here in Charleston visiting us for two weeks bringing us lots of treats from Germany. They are most definitely The Grand Marshall family of our Markt! Thank you, Conny and The Lord for our longtime providential relationship and your effect on our lives and others. Amazing! #christkindlmarktusa #christkindlmarktchs #charlestonchristmas #germanchristmasmarket

Sign up at the link in our bio to volunteer for CHRISTkindlmarkt 2023. We have 3 different teams with numerous time slots available. The details are listed below:

•All volunteers will receive one complimentary ticket per person to attend another Markt. 
•Minimum age to volunteer is 15. For a bar service volunteer, you must be 21+.

•All shifts are 5 hours and are detailed out in our spreadsheet.

If anyone does not believe the Lord hears our prayers and has the power to grant miracles - let me tell you a story this Lord’s Day for His glory and your belief. CHRISTkindlmarkt CHS 2023 initially had rain predicted 5 of the 6 days of Markt. Many prayed along beside us for “no rain during Markt”. Despite raining all around us each of those days CKMC was completely spared from rain…until the last closing day when it rained only 10 min. Most took cover and enjoyed clear skies after. All had a great attitude and we are so grateful. AND THEN today 12/17 ….one week later we are underwater all around the grounds. These chairs are beside the LGB German outdoor train and are underwater due to the high tide and the downpour. There is no vendor street in front of the huts it’s all water. The entry at the sign is 12 inches under. His Spirit is here with us just as Christmas is the gift of His presence every day - God with us, Christ is born, and His presence is real. Merry Christmas, worship and adore the King of Kings who is absolute love. I can’t thank Christ enough for daily gifts of grace like the timing in our favor of rain.
